- Created using the 'new' keyword 

Example: 

// Declaration

User u; 

// Instantiation (allocates memory)

u = new User(); 

u.name="John";
u.printName(); 

// My name is John


- A class has many objects (instances)

Example: 

public class User {
  // fields and methods defining a User
}

User joe = new User(); 
joe.name = "Joe"; 
joe.printName();


User billy = new User(); 
billy.name = "Billy";
billy.printName(); 

